00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:07,654 --> 00:00:08,905
[lighter flicks]

2
00:00:19,041 --> 00:00:20,667
[exhales]

3
00:00:33,430 --> 00:00:35,474
[exhales]

4
00:00:37,643 --> 00:00:40,562
Ah, shit. I really thought
you'd do better than this.

5
00:00:42,230 --> 00:00:43,231
[clicks tongue]

6
00:00:48,278 --> 00:00:50,072
Why are you giving me this?

7
00:00:50,155 --> 00:00:53,116
Sunok, I think I really like you.

8
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,326
You like me?

9
00:00:54,409 --> 00:00:55,410
Yeah.

10
00:00:59,414 --> 00:01:01,875
[Sunok giggles]
Hold on.

11
00:01:01,958 --> 00:01:03,710
[Male News Reporter] Up next...

12
00:01:03,794 --> 00:01:05,754
[Friend A] Pretty sure it's my turn.

13
00:01:05,837 --> 00:01:07,464
And here's the ribbon!

14
00:01:07,547 --> 00:01:08,632
[Friend B] Whoa!

15
00:01:08,715 --> 00:01:10,926
[Male News Reporter] In an effort
to boost areas hit hard by the decline

16
00:01:11,009 --> 00:01:12,219
of the coal industry...

17
00:01:12,302 --> 00:01:13,637
Hey, where's Sunok?

18
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:15,055
-Mm, not sure.
-[Friend B] I don't know where she is.

19
00:01:15,138 --> 00:01:16,264
GOLD LAND HOTEL &amp; RESORT CONSTRUCTION SITE

20
00:01:16,348 --> 00:01:17,849
-[Friend A] Sunok needs to see this.
-[Friend B] She must be somewhere.

21
00:01:19,518 --> 00:01:20,769
[drum clangs]

22
00:01:21,937 --> 00:01:24,690
[gagging and struggling]

23
00:01:29,569 --> 00:01:32,114
[short gasps]

24
00:01:32,197 --> 00:01:33,198
[Henchman A] What the...

25
00:01:33,281 --> 00:01:34,491
Shit!

26
00:01:34,574 --> 00:01:35,575
[Henchman B] This crazy bastard!

27
00:01:35,659 --> 00:01:36,827
[Henchman A] Hold him, hold him!

28
00:01:36,910 --> 00:01:38,495
-[Henchman B] Fuck me.
-[Henchman A] That way.

29
00:01:39,621 --> 00:01:41,123
[Chairman Ahn] Come on.

30
00:01:41,206 --> 00:01:43,542
Don't be so rash.
You're still young.

31
00:01:44,709 --> 00:01:47,170
What you should be doing is working
to pay off your debts.

32
00:01:48,380 --> 00:01:50,841
How could I ever pay it all back?

33
00:01:50,924 --> 00:01:52,801
[Chairman Ahn laughing]
I know, right?

34
00:01:52,884 --> 00:01:54,678
On your police salary?

35
00:01:55,512 --> 00:01:58,223
Well, you should've known your place
before pushing it so far.

36
00:01:58,306 --> 00:01:59,558
[Young Jinman] I know, I know.

37
00:02:00,142 --> 00:02:03,145
Just kill me,
and only me, okay?

38
00:02:03,228 --> 00:02:05,772
But please leave
that innocent woman alone.

39
00:02:05,856 --> 00:02:07,107
I'm begging you.

40
00:02:07,732 --> 00:02:09,443
You don't need to pay us back.

41
00:02:10,277 --> 00:02:11,570
At least not entirely with money.

42
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:14,740
[Chairman Ahn] Constable Kim Jinman.

43
00:02:16,575 --> 00:02:17,576
What if...

44
00:02:20,287 --> 00:02:22,414
You became my man instead, yeah?

45
00:02:26,001 --> 00:02:29,004
[♪ dramatic music]

46
00:03:01,745 --> 00:03:05,040
[♪ music continues]

47
00:03:13,507 --> 00:03:15,342
[inhales deeply]

48
00:03:15,425 --> 00:03:16,802
[exhales]

49
00:03:20,764 --> 00:03:23,767
[♪ sad piano music]
STYLE
::cue()

50
00:03:45,872 --> 00:03:48,875
[♪ music continues]

51
00:04:04,182 --> 00:04:05,850
EPISODE 7
VILLAINS

52
00:04:05,934 --> 00:04:08,937
[metal detector beeping]

53
00:04:17,112 --> 00:04:18,113
[light clicks]

54
00:04:18,196 --> 00:04:19,197
[items dropping]

55
00:04:20,073 --> 00:04:21,825
Why are you here?

56
00:04:23,618 --> 00:04:24,953
H-Heeju.

57
00:04:25,412 --> 00:04:26,621
[Heeju exhales]

58
00:04:27,581 --> 00:04:29,541
I told you not to come here, didn't I?

59
00:04:30,250 --> 00:04:32,335
-The gold bars aren't here.
-[Dokyung] Let's not do this.

60
00:04:32,919 --> 00:04:35,964
Let's just take the gold
and leave together.

61
00:04:36,047 --> 00:04:37,799
[Dokyung] I already made
the deal with the buyers.

62
00:04:37,883 --> 00:04:40,552
All we need to do is go to Cambodia
and show them the gold bars.

63
00:04:40,635 --> 00:04:42,637
We'll have 100 billion won in our account!

64
00:04:43,555 --> 00:04:45,056
I'm already giving you half.

65
00:04:45,849 --> 00:04:47,267
Isn't that enough?

66
00:04:47,350 --> 00:04:49,686
-Do you really have to take it all?
-Heeju.

67
00:04:57,402 --> 00:04:58,862
Heeju, what happened to you?

68
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:01,907
Why are you doing this?

69
00:05:06,912 --> 00:05:07,913
[exhales sharply]

70
00:05:14,628 --> 00:05:16,129
So this is what it was like.

71
00:05:17,589 --> 00:05:18,965
The place you grew up in.

72
00:05:21,217 --> 00:05:22,802
[Dokyung] You said it was hell.

73
00:05:22,886 --> 00:05:24,387
So why are you here again?

74
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:26,806
What happened to you?

75
00:05:28,934 --> 00:05:29,935
[inhales sharply]

76
00:05:30,685 --> 00:05:32,562
Look, if this is because
of something I've done...

77
00:05:34,272 --> 00:05:36,191
...at least give me a chance
to explain myself.

78
00:05:37,275 --> 00:05:39,653
You can do that, can't you?
After all we've been through?

79
00:05:41,446 --> 00:05:42,447
Dokyung.

80
00:05:44,532 --> 00:05:45,742
Look at us right now.

81
00:05:48,328 --> 00:05:49,496
This is the reason.

82
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:52,540
This is why we shouldn't
be together any longer.

83
00:05:54,292 --> 00:05:55,710
Nothing happened.

84
00:05:55,794 --> 00:05:57,253
And we're not bad people.

85
00:05:58,380 --> 00:06:00,006
This is just how life is.

86
00:06:01,466 --> 00:06:03,259
When you win something really big.

87
00:06:05,261 --> 00:06:07,013
You have to lose something else.

88
00:06:07,973 --> 00:06:09,474
A thing that's less precious.

89
00:06:10,433 --> 00:06:11,601
[Heeju] And quite frankly...

90
00:06:12,769 --> 00:06:15,313
...I'm the one who has the gold now.
It's mine.

91
00:06:15,397 --> 00:06:17,816
It's up to me whether I share
it with you or not.

92
00:06:19,317 --> 00:06:20,318
Heeju.

93
00:06:22,278 --> 00:06:23,321
Get out.

94
00:06:24,823 --> 00:06:26,408
And don't ever look for me again.

95
00:06:28,451 --> 00:06:30,078
[Heeju] It's true that because of you...

96
00:06:31,162 --> 00:06:33,665
...I finally got out of the hell hole
I'd been living in.

97
00:06:35,333 --> 00:06:37,085
And being with you made me happy.

98
00:06:38,420 --> 00:06:41,631
But we can't be happy together anymore.
That's why it needs to end.

99
00:07:03,361 --> 00:07:07,991
[door creaks open and closed]

100
00:07:08,074 --> 00:07:09,409
[sniffles]

101
00:07:12,954 --> 00:07:15,957
[breathing shakily]
STYLE
::cue()

102
00:07:19,002 --> 00:07:20,545
[camera shutter clicking]

103
00:07:20,628 --> 00:07:23,631
[indistinct quiet chattering]

104
00:07:25,341 --> 00:07:28,344
[camera shutters clicking]

105
00:07:31,181 --> 00:07:32,265
-Thank you.
-Oh.

106
00:07:32,348 --> 00:07:33,475
Thank you very much.

107
00:07:33,558 --> 00:07:35,018
[both chuckling]

108
00:07:35,101 --> 00:07:38,104
[applause]

109
00:07:39,230 --> 00:07:40,231
That's great to hear.

110
00:07:40,315 --> 00:07:42,275
[all laughing]

111
00:07:42,358 --> 00:07:44,110
-And so it begins.
-Ah, look who it is!

112
00:07:44,194 --> 00:07:45,945
Sir, you're here.

113
00:07:46,029 --> 00:07:48,448
-[Governor] Mr. Ahn.
-Thank you for coming. I know you're busy.

114
00:07:48,531 --> 00:07:49,783
Well, how could I miss it?

115
00:07:49,866 --> 00:07:51,493
It's your business, Mr. Ahn.

116
00:07:51,576 --> 00:07:52,702
[all laughing]

117
00:07:52,786 --> 00:07:54,788
Oh, right.
This is our partner from Cambodia.

118
00:07:54,871 --> 00:07:55,872
-Ah.
-Our governor.

119
00:07:55,955 --> 00:07:57,040
-How do you do?
-Nice to meet you.

120
00:07:57,123 --> 00:07:58,124
-[Governor] Congratulations.
-[Socom] Thank you.

121
00:07:58,208 --> 00:07:59,793
-[Governor] Of course.
-[Socom] Yes.

122
00:07:59,876 --> 00:08:01,044
-Thank you.
-Thank you very much.

123
00:08:01,127 --> 00:08:02,086
-[Socom] Thank you.
-[Governor] It's been a pleasure.

124
00:08:02,170 --> 00:08:03,129
[Socom] Absolutely.

125
00:08:03,213 --> 00:08:04,172
[Chairman Ahn] And this
is the congressman.

126
00:08:04,255 --> 00:08:05,882
[Politician] I've been looking forward
to meeting you.

127
00:08:05,965 --> 00:08:08,968
[Chairman Ahn chewing and slurping]

128
00:08:12,013 --> 00:08:13,973
The actors played their parts well.

129
00:08:15,266 --> 00:08:17,018
Make sure everyone keeps their mouth shut.

130
00:08:17,101 --> 00:08:18,353
No loose lips.

131
00:08:19,938 --> 00:08:21,940
And I want this deal on
the front page tomorrow.

132
00:08:22,023 --> 00:08:23,233
Understood, sir.

133
00:08:24,567 --> 00:08:25,985
Those Cambodians.

134
00:08:26,069 --> 00:08:28,154
Stick 'em in a room and keep 'em happy.

135
00:08:28,613 --> 00:08:30,657
Drugs, drinks, women, whatever it takes.

136
00:08:30,740 --> 00:08:32,075
Don't want 'em getting ideas.

137
00:08:32,158 --> 00:08:33,785
-Yes, sir.
-[Chairman Ahn slurping]

138
00:08:33,868 --> 00:08:36,412
Ah, all this bullshit
for one single casket!

139
00:08:37,288 --> 00:08:38,289
[Jinman] Hello, sir.

140
00:08:38,373 --> 00:08:39,374
It's been a while.

141
00:08:51,302 --> 00:08:53,054
Where's the casket?

142
00:08:53,138 --> 00:08:54,139
[Chairman Ahn] Who took it?

143
00:08:55,390 --> 00:08:57,934
Yeah, well, it's, uh...

144
00:08:59,561 --> 00:09:00,562
It was this woman, right?

145
00:09:02,438 --> 00:09:03,690
-Yeah.
-[Jinman] It was?

146
00:09:03,773 --> 00:09:06,067
-[Donggu] Yeah.
-Look, different name.

147
00:09:06,693 --> 00:09:09,070
[Jinman] So it wasn't Cha Yujin.
It was Kim Heeju.

148
00:09:11,739 --> 00:09:13,616
The thing is, sir,
it's just...

149
00:09:14,367 --> 00:09:16,744
...we're talkin' about one ton
of gold bars, here.

150
00:09:16,828 --> 00:09:18,580
And having to smuggle and sell it?

151
00:09:19,414 --> 00:09:21,499
I don't think anyone could do
that by themselves.

152
00:09:22,458 --> 00:09:23,543
They must have had help.

153
00:09:23,626 --> 00:09:25,295
Someone else is pulling the strings?

154
00:09:26,921 --> 00:09:28,047
Suspect anyone?

155
00:09:28,131 --> 00:09:29,382
[Jinman] We'll find out
once we investigate.

156
00:09:30,758 --> 00:09:35,638
Although, with the police being involved,
it can get pretty risky.

157
00:09:35,722 --> 00:09:36,806
Do you want cash?

158
00:09:36,890 --> 00:09:37,891
[Jinman] Well, I...

159
00:09:39,142 --> 00:09:41,936
...I do always need more money, sir.

160
00:09:42,562 --> 00:09:43,980
How much you want?

161
00:09:44,898 --> 00:09:46,816
One gold bar.
That's it.

162
00:09:46,900 --> 00:09:47,901
That's all I want.

163
00:09:49,152 --> 00:09:50,528
[Jinman] Give me a week to work on this.

164
00:09:51,779 --> 00:09:53,615
I'll find all 100 gold bars.

165
00:09:54,908 --> 00:09:56,409
Keep one for myself.

166
00:09:56,492 --> 00:10:00,622
And then I'll return
the other 99 back to you, sir.

167
00:10:01,122 --> 00:10:02,999
What do you plan to do with one gold bar?

168
00:10:03,082 --> 00:10:06,586
Well, uh, you know,
I'm getting old now.

169
00:10:07,879 --> 00:10:09,797
I'm thinking of quitting the force.

170
00:10:09,881 --> 00:10:11,716
[Jinman] I wanna buy a pawnshop.

171
00:10:11,799 --> 00:10:14,260
Sit back and take it easy.
Play loan shark.

172
00:10:14,761 --> 00:10:16,387
[Jinman] Just live like that.

173
00:10:16,471 --> 00:10:20,016
I think I've done more than enough, sir.
That's a good end for me.

174
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:25,230
[Chairman Ahn scoffs]
Sure.

175
00:10:26,105 --> 00:10:28,191
Bring the casket back,
and I'll give you one.

176
00:10:30,735 --> 00:10:31,986
[Jinman] Thank you, sir.

177
00:10:34,155 --> 00:10:35,740
If you need to get in touch,

178
00:10:35,823 --> 00:10:37,408
-go through Chief Cheon.
-Yes.

179
00:10:39,369 --> 00:10:42,080
Well, then, we have an agreement.
Excuse me.

180
00:10:44,457 --> 00:10:45,792
-[Chairman Ahn] Hey, Kim Jinman.
-Yes, sir.

181
00:10:47,335 --> 00:10:50,672
You knew about the gold all along
and you didn't lose your cool.
STYLE
::cue()

182
00:10:51,756 --> 00:10:53,007
[Chairman Ahn] You were first, right?

183
00:10:53,299 --> 00:10:54,384
To find out about it?

184
00:10:54,926 --> 00:10:56,844
You're the one who told Hocheol.

185
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:58,763
But you never thought...

186
00:11:00,098 --> 00:11:02,558
"Should I just keep all the gold
and run away?"

187
00:11:02,642 --> 00:11:04,394
You never felt the urge
to do anything like that?

188
00:11:04,477 --> 00:11:05,687
[chewing]

189
00:11:06,813 --> 00:11:09,691
No, how could I?
I wouldn't touch your property, sir.

190
00:11:09,774 --> 00:11:11,067
[Chairman Ahn chuckles]

191
00:11:12,151 --> 00:11:13,194
[laughs]

192
00:11:13,278 --> 00:11:14,279
Right.

193
00:11:15,321 --> 00:11:17,240
You've always played it small,
haven't you?

194
00:11:18,866 --> 00:11:20,785
I once told him I'd take
his wife's kidney.

195
00:11:20,868 --> 00:11:23,579
[laughs]
He tried to hang himself.

196
00:11:23,663 --> 00:11:25,540
That's how freaked out he was.

197
00:11:26,249 --> 00:11:28,501
So I said I'd spare her life.

198
00:11:28,584 --> 00:11:32,588
And this man starts grovelling, begging.
"I'll do anything you say!"

199
00:11:33,756 --> 00:11:35,258
Just crying.

200
00:11:35,341 --> 00:11:37,427
[laughing]

201
00:11:37,510 --> 00:11:41,055
And that-that's why I like you,
Kim Jinman!

202
00:11:41,139 --> 00:11:42,598
You're still useful!

203
00:11:42,682 --> 00:11:45,685
[Chairman Ahn laughing]

204
00:11:48,438 --> 00:11:51,232
[Kang] Four five two one. No.

205
00:11:51,316 --> 00:11:53,192
How about this one here?

206
00:11:53,276 --> 00:11:55,236
JANGGAK TRADE INC.

207
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:56,654
That's not it, either.

208
00:11:57,447 --> 00:11:59,615
Four three two oh.
Four three two oh.

209
00:11:59,699 --> 00:12:00,742
[grunts]

210
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:05,079
[cell phone vibrating]

211
00:12:05,163 --> 00:12:07,582
Ah, shit.
What is it now?

212
00:12:10,543 --> 00:12:11,711
Yeah, what is it?

213
00:12:11,794 --> 00:12:14,714
[Jinman] Are you looking for
a five two seven nine Santa Fe?

214
00:12:14,797 --> 00:12:15,798
Yes.

215
00:12:16,507 --> 00:12:18,593
[Jinman] I'm here, fucker. Here.

216
00:12:18,676 --> 00:12:20,094
[clicks tongue]
Shit.

217
00:12:25,099 --> 00:12:27,852
Hey. I checked all
the cars here earlier today.

218
00:12:28,519 --> 00:12:29,520
It's not here.

219
00:12:31,272 --> 00:12:33,316
So then Park made you do this?

220
00:12:33,399 --> 00:12:35,443
No, Chairman Ahn.

221
00:12:35,526 --> 00:12:36,652
[groans]

222
00:12:36,736 --> 00:12:38,404
[Kang] Fuck, this is driving me crazy.

223
00:12:38,738 --> 00:12:39,906
[lip smacks]

224
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:42,784
Hey, what's with that car, anyways?

225
00:12:43,368 --> 00:12:44,369
Is it Cha Yujin's?

226
00:12:44,869 --> 00:12:46,120
Well, I don't know.

227
00:12:49,415 --> 00:12:50,416
[Jinman] Hey.

228
00:12:51,667 --> 00:12:52,668
Thought you said you were done.

229
00:12:52,752 --> 00:12:55,338
You weren't gonna work for Geumsong,
so why are you?

230
00:12:56,005 --> 00:12:57,215
We lost Lee Dokyung.

231
00:12:58,758 --> 00:12:59,759
[both exhale sharply]

232
00:12:59,842 --> 00:13:00,843
[Jinman] Gosh.

233
00:13:00,927 --> 00:13:02,970
The department's already giving me hell
for this.

234
00:13:03,346 --> 00:13:04,555
Now the director, too.

235
00:13:05,223 --> 00:13:06,224
[clicks tongue]

236
00:13:09,102 --> 00:13:10,937
Just call it a night for now, yeah?

237
00:13:11,979 --> 00:13:15,316
My best guess is that there's a good
chance they got rid of it already.

238
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,402
Probably dumped it in
a reservoir or something.

239
00:13:18,861 --> 00:13:22,198
Just tell Park that the car belonged
to Janggak Trading.

240
00:13:23,366 --> 00:13:25,201
[Kang] Right.
Yeah, that's a good call.

241
00:13:25,284 --> 00:13:26,285
Yeah.

242
00:13:28,955 --> 00:13:30,039
[exhales]

243
00:13:30,123 --> 00:13:33,126
[cell phone vibrating]

244
00:13:37,713 --> 00:13:38,714
You find it yet?

245
00:13:39,424 --> 00:13:41,342
[Kang] Uh, no.
No, not exactly.

246
00:13:42,885 --> 00:13:44,971
[inhales deeply]

247
00:13:46,722 --> 00:13:48,391
You're a stupid fuck.
You know that?

248
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:55,690
Now wait. You see,
it's not a private vehicle.

249
00:13:55,773 --> 00:13:57,233
It belongs to a company.

250
00:13:58,067 --> 00:13:59,277
Fuck, which one?

251
00:13:59,735 --> 00:14:00,987
[Kang] It's called Janggak Trading.

252
00:14:01,696 --> 00:14:03,531
It looks like a trading company,

253
00:14:03,614 --> 00:14:05,658
but they buy cheap Chinese cars
and sell them overseas.

254
00:14:06,409 --> 00:14:07,577
Heo Donggu's company?

255
00:14:08,369 --> 00:14:09,996
[Kang] Yeah.
Do you know it?

256
00:14:11,998 --> 00:14:13,040
Good work.

257
00:14:14,041 --> 00:14:15,042
[phone beeps]
STYLE
::cue()

258
00:14:17,211 --> 00:14:20,214
[car engine rumbling]

259
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:22,216
[Woogy] It's because my dad
suddenly collapsed.

260
00:14:22,300 --> 00:14:23,301
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

261
00:14:23,801 --> 00:14:26,679
I need to leave so I can help
him out on his farm.

262
00:14:27,221 --> 00:14:28,347
You're an orphan.

263
00:14:28,431 --> 00:14:29,640
Uh...

264
00:14:31,309 --> 00:14:33,060
...he's actually my uncle, not my dad.

265
00:14:33,144 --> 00:14:36,397
Do you think we're a real company
'cause we pay you a salary?

266
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:38,608
You've always been able
to walk in as you please.

267
00:14:39,275 --> 00:14:41,569
I'll cut off your ear
if you wanna walk out, though.

268
00:14:42,987 --> 00:14:45,281
-Yes, I understand.
-You understand?

269
00:14:46,282 --> 00:14:47,617
Seriously?

270
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:49,952
Just think it over.

271
00:14:50,036 --> 00:14:52,163
[Gitae] You won't make this kind
of money anywhere else.

272
00:14:52,246 --> 00:14:54,123
And you're one of our best.

273
00:14:55,625 --> 00:14:56,626
[door opens]

274
00:14:56,709 --> 00:14:58,753
Now get out.
Go on.

275
00:14:58,836 --> 00:15:01,505
Back to work, now!
Go, go, go, go.

276
00:15:05,259 --> 00:15:06,260
Hey.

277
00:15:11,224 --> 00:15:12,225
Sir.

278
00:15:15,519 --> 00:15:16,854
It was you.

279
00:15:16,938 --> 00:15:19,440
[both grunting]

280
00:15:21,025 --> 00:15:22,026
No, it wasn't!

281
00:15:24,237 --> 00:15:25,446
What do you mean?

282
00:15:27,573 --> 00:15:30,159
You're that kid whose ear
I almost took off, right?

283
00:15:31,911 --> 00:15:34,288
Uh, yes. That's correct.
[clears throat]

284
00:15:35,957 --> 00:15:37,041
It's still on there.

285
00:15:37,124 --> 00:15:39,627
Yes. It healed up well.

286
00:15:44,257 --> 00:15:45,383
Go on.

287
00:15:49,470 --> 00:15:52,181
[door creaking]

288
00:15:54,642 --> 00:15:55,685
[Gitae] Boss.

289
00:15:56,310 --> 00:15:57,603
Have a seat over here.

290
00:15:57,687 --> 00:15:59,272
[Gitae] Or should I call you President?

291
00:15:59,355 --> 00:16:01,148
You think I dragged myself here...

292
00:16:01,232 --> 00:16:02,316
[inhales]

293
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:04,110
...just so I can sit in that chair again?

294
00:16:04,193 --> 00:16:07,530
That's true.
[laughs]

295
00:16:09,573 --> 00:16:11,117
Gitae, let's find the casket.

296
00:16:11,659 --> 00:16:13,160
Do you even know where it is?

297
00:16:15,037 --> 00:16:16,747
Well, come on, then!

298
00:16:16,831 --> 00:16:18,291
Let's go get it!

299
00:16:18,374 --> 00:16:21,043
And then, boom, your honor is back!

300
00:16:21,669 --> 00:16:22,795
[Gitae] We have to!

301
00:16:24,964 --> 00:16:28,843
[chuckling]

302
00:16:30,428 --> 00:16:31,887
[Woojin] It's Detective Kim.

303
00:16:31,971 --> 00:16:34,098
He thinks Janggak Trading is behind this.

304
00:16:34,890 --> 00:16:36,434
[Chairman Ahn] Janggak Trading?

305
00:16:36,517 --> 00:16:39,437
He told me you'd recognize
what that refers to.

306
00:16:40,271 --> 00:16:41,272
[grunts]

307
00:16:43,357 --> 00:16:44,650
[exhales]

308
00:16:46,694 --> 00:16:47,820
What's Janggak Trading?

309
00:16:48,571 --> 00:16:52,366
Oh, hello, sir.
Uh, it's Heo Donggu's company. Yeah.

310
00:16:52,450 --> 00:16:55,328
He was the man you kicked out, uh,
about ten years ago.

311
00:16:55,619 --> 00:16:57,830
-[Chairman Ahn] Oh.
-You remember, right?

312
00:16:57,913 --> 00:16:59,749
Okay, stay there.
Keep an eye on him.

313
00:17:01,375 --> 00:17:02,376
[phone beeps]

314
00:17:06,172 --> 00:17:09,008
Grab a few guys.
Head to Janggak Trading.

315
00:17:09,216 --> 00:17:10,217
When you get there,

316
00:17:10,301 --> 00:17:13,637
cut off Heo Donggu's other ear
and find the casket. Get moving.

317
00:17:14,305 --> 00:17:15,765
Yes, sir.

318
00:17:15,848 --> 00:17:17,892
[Man] Ah, let's go.

319
00:17:17,975 --> 00:17:19,268
[Woogy] Janggak Trading?

320
00:17:19,977 --> 00:17:20,978
Mm-hmm.

321
00:17:22,229 --> 00:17:23,814
You know what those guys do, right?

322
00:17:23,898 --> 00:17:25,232
And you're buying a ferry ticket there?

323
00:17:25,316 --> 00:17:26,609
[Heeju] I know.

324
00:17:27,360 --> 00:17:28,527
I got the car there.

325
00:17:30,988 --> 00:17:32,657
And that's where I got the bullets, too.

326
00:17:33,532 --> 00:17:36,410
Ah, just give half the gold bars
to Dokyung and let him figure it out!

327
00:17:37,078 --> 00:17:39,705
That bastard is an expert at smuggling!
He'll know what to do!

328
00:17:43,334 --> 00:17:46,295
[Woogy] Heeju, seriously.
What are you thinking? Huh?

329
00:17:47,129 --> 00:17:48,130
We're not doing this.

330
00:17:48,673 --> 00:17:49,674
'Kay?

331
00:17:50,466 --> 00:17:53,761
You're giving him half the gold.
Buying a ferry ticket.

332
00:17:54,178 --> 00:17:55,763
[Woogy] You can't think like that anymore.

333
00:17:56,847 --> 00:17:58,683
We have to start looking out
for ourselves first.

334
00:18:02,478 --> 00:18:03,854
[exhales]
[silverware clatters]

335
00:18:07,149 --> 00:18:08,317
[exhales sharply]
STYLE
::cue()

336
00:18:14,407 --> 00:18:19,704
JG JANGGAK TRADE INC.
TRADING/ TRANSPORT/ LOGISTICS

337
00:18:27,336 --> 00:18:28,713
[car engine shuts off]

338
00:18:29,630 --> 00:18:30,631
Heeju.

339
00:18:37,179 --> 00:18:38,347
The gold bars.

340
00:18:39,432 --> 00:18:40,641
Why don't you just tell me where they are?

341
00:18:41,934 --> 00:18:43,394
It'd be just in case.

342
00:18:43,477 --> 00:18:46,605
If anything bad were to happen to you,
then don't you think I should know?

343
00:18:46,689 --> 00:18:47,982
Woogy.

344
00:18:48,065 --> 00:18:49,066
Why don't we do this?

345
00:18:49,859 --> 00:18:51,277
You could schedule an E-mail.

346
00:18:51,360 --> 00:18:53,446
Write it in there,
set it to send later.

347
00:18:53,529 --> 00:18:55,823
And if you come back safely,
you could just delete it.

348
00:18:57,283 --> 00:18:59,285
So then if I were to come back safely...

349
00:19:00,202 --> 00:19:01,579
...you would just kill me, right?

350
00:19:03,414 --> 00:19:05,166
Right, I see why you'd think that.

351
00:19:06,959 --> 00:19:08,502
Heeju, just be careful.

352
00:19:08,586 --> 00:19:10,129
-I really mean it, okay?
-Okay.

353
00:19:10,212 --> 00:19:12,673
Seriously, those guys can be crazy.
You need to watch your back.

354
00:19:18,471 --> 00:19:20,723
[inhales and exhales sharply]

355
00:19:27,438 --> 00:19:28,439
[Jinman] Kim Heeju?

356
00:19:35,321 --> 00:19:36,363
What is this?

357
00:19:38,115 --> 00:19:39,116
[Donggu] Anywhere?

358
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:42,161
I see.

359
00:19:44,455 --> 00:19:48,125
There's a ferry leaving Mokcheon Port
in two days, if that works for you.

360
00:19:48,209 --> 00:19:49,752
What are you loading?

361
00:19:49,835 --> 00:19:51,337
There's one car.

362
00:19:52,254 --> 00:19:53,464
And one passenger.

363
00:19:53,547 --> 00:19:54,840
Stow away?

364
00:19:56,217 --> 00:19:57,384
[Donggu exhales]

365
00:19:58,552 --> 00:20:00,554
That's not a cheap thing to do, you know.

366
00:20:01,597 --> 00:20:04,892
Ten million, even 20 million won
just won't cut it.

367
00:20:04,975 --> 00:20:07,353
These days,
pocket change isn't enough.

368
00:20:12,107 --> 00:20:13,734
[Heeju] Take this up front.

369
00:20:13,818 --> 00:20:16,904
Once the transport is done,
I'll give you another one.

370
00:20:29,667 --> 00:20:33,003
All right, Park, you asshole.
Just show up already.

371
00:20:35,673 --> 00:20:36,715
[tires squeak]

372
00:20:36,799 --> 00:20:38,133
[car door opens]

373
00:20:40,302 --> 00:20:42,179
[cell phone trilling]

374
00:20:42,263 --> 00:20:43,430
[Jinman] Hey, yeah, Chief Cheon.

375
00:20:43,514 --> 00:20:45,182
Park is here right now.
You coming or what?

376
00:20:47,184 --> 00:20:48,978
[Woogy] Is that Park?

377
00:20:52,982 --> 00:20:54,942
HEEJU, DIRECTOR PARK IS HERE.

378
00:20:55,025 --> 00:20:56,861
[cell phone vibrates]
[Donggu exhales]

379
00:21:00,030 --> 00:21:01,448
GET OUT OF THERE RIGHT NOW.

380
00:21:02,533 --> 00:21:03,576
What?

381
00:21:05,119 --> 00:21:06,829
[gasping]

382
00:21:07,663 --> 00:21:11,584
[Donggu] Wait. Did you mess around
with Geumseong's stuff?

383
00:21:11,667 --> 00:21:16,046
You did! Come here! Come over here!
Quickly! Go, go, go, go, go!

384
00:21:16,130 --> 00:21:17,715
Hide here!

385
00:21:18,799 --> 00:21:21,802
In here! Okay. Inside this!
You need to get in. Okay.

386
00:21:21,886 --> 00:21:25,514
They won't find you in here. Here!
Don't even breathe! Okay?

387
00:21:25,598 --> 00:21:28,350
Don't make any noise!
You need to stay hidden in here!

388
00:21:28,434 --> 00:21:30,686
[Donggu breathing erratically]
Okay, good. Good.

389
00:21:30,769 --> 00:21:32,938
[heavy breathing]

390
00:21:33,939 --> 00:21:35,983
[bullets clattering on floor]
Oh, fuck me!

391
00:21:37,067 --> 00:21:38,819
Oh, gosh, I don't know!

392
00:21:38,903 --> 00:21:40,070
Ah!

393
00:21:41,280 --> 00:21:43,616
Hey there, Donggu.
It's been a while.

394
00:21:43,699 --> 00:21:46,243
[groaning]

395
00:21:46,952 --> 00:21:50,331
Hey, I think there was a misunderstanding,
right?

396
00:21:51,332 --> 00:21:52,249
[Donggu] What?

397
00:21:52,333 --> 00:21:54,835
[all shouting]
[glass shattering]

398
00:21:54,919 --> 00:21:57,755
[Donggu whimpering]

399
00:21:57,838 --> 00:21:59,423
You know I don't say things I don't mean.

400
00:21:59,506 --> 00:22:01,634
[Hocheol] Where'd you hide the casket?

401
00:22:02,176 --> 00:22:04,136
Tell me or I'll take your other ear.

402
00:22:04,219 --> 00:22:05,596
This is all a misunderstanding!

403
00:22:05,679 --> 00:22:08,724
This isn't a funeral home!
Why would you look for a casket here?

404
00:22:08,807 --> 00:22:10,392
Wait!

405
00:22:10,893 --> 00:22:13,896
[screaming]

406
00:22:16,148 --> 00:22:17,191
Stop it!

407
00:22:17,650 --> 00:22:20,361
[Doggu screaming]
STYLE
::cue()

408
00:22:24,657 --> 00:22:26,158
[tires squealing]

409
00:22:26,659 --> 00:22:28,577
What the actual fuck?

410
00:22:28,661 --> 00:22:29,662
[Woojin] Get up there!

411
00:22:33,958 --> 00:22:35,209
[coughs]

412
00:22:37,628 --> 00:22:39,254
[Donggu screaming]

413
00:22:39,338 --> 00:22:42,967
Ju! Ju Haran! Ah!
It's Ju Haran!

414
00:22:43,050 --> 00:22:44,426
It's Ju Haran!

415
00:22:44,510 --> 00:22:46,178
Who is Ju Haran?

416
00:22:46,261 --> 00:22:49,264
[Donggu screaming]

417
00:22:50,391 --> 00:22:52,017
[banging on door]

418
00:22:52,101 --> 00:22:53,227
[Gitae] Oh, shit!

419
00:22:53,310 --> 00:22:55,354
[banging continues]
Hey, boss!

420
00:22:55,437 --> 00:22:56,772
-[Gitae] Hurry!
-Fuck's sake!

421
00:22:56,855 --> 00:22:57,898
Ju Haran!
Who the fuck is she?

422
00:22:57,982 --> 00:22:59,233
I'm answering you!

423
00:22:59,316 --> 00:23:00,317
[Gitae shouts]

424
00:23:00,401 --> 00:23:02,236
[Gitae groans]

425
00:23:02,319 --> 00:23:04,238
[shouting]

426
00:23:05,447 --> 00:23:06,740
Fuck, it reeks in here.

427
00:23:06,824 --> 00:23:08,575
[Donggu wailing]

428
00:23:08,659 --> 00:23:09,743
What's this?

429
00:23:09,827 --> 00:23:12,329
This a Geumsong Alumni reunion?

430
00:23:12,413 --> 00:23:14,248
[Woojin laughs]

431
00:23:15,457 --> 00:23:17,001
Ah, come on.

432
00:23:17,626 --> 00:23:19,336
I'm really disappointed in you, Park.

433
00:23:20,129 --> 00:23:21,547
[Woojin] The chairman gave you a chance.

434
00:23:22,339 --> 00:23:23,424
But you know what you are?

435
00:23:24,508 --> 00:23:25,884
You're too old school.

436
00:23:26,427 --> 00:23:27,761
It's fucking pathetic.

437
00:23:29,013 --> 00:23:30,681
Both of you are.

438
00:23:30,764 --> 00:23:31,932
You thought you could take
the chairman's casket

439
00:23:32,016 --> 00:23:33,308
and just get away with it?

440
00:23:33,392 --> 00:23:35,102
It was a rhetorical question, you fuck.

441
00:23:35,686 --> 00:23:37,813
[Woojin] 'Kay, last chance.

442
00:23:38,522 --> 00:23:40,315
Who'd like to be the first to talk?

443
00:23:40,399 --> 00:23:42,192
Where's the casket?

444
00:23:42,276 --> 00:23:43,819
Okay, listen. It's not like that.

445
00:23:43,902 --> 00:23:46,030
The boss and I came here for Donggu.

446
00:23:46,113 --> 00:23:47,740
-He's the one who stole the casket.
-[Donggu] Bullshit!

447
00:23:47,823 --> 00:23:49,950
-He took it.
-I don't fucking have it, you liar!

448
00:23:50,701 --> 00:23:52,953
[whimpers]
Just, fuck.

449
00:23:53,037 --> 00:23:54,747
Just give me a second to explain!

450
00:23:54,830 --> 00:23:56,123
[Donggu] That car?

451
00:23:56,206 --> 00:23:59,334
A week ago a lady called Ju Haran came by
and bought it from me.

452
00:23:59,418 --> 00:24:01,170
-Ju Haran, huh?
-[Donggu] Fuck, how many times

453
00:24:01,253 --> 00:24:03,422
do I have to tell you?
How do I explain this?

454
00:24:03,505 --> 00:24:05,674
I have no idea, really!
I don't know!

455
00:24:05,758 --> 00:24:07,426
I've never once seen the casket!

456
00:24:07,509 --> 00:24:09,803
[Donggu] All I did was to sell a car
to this woman named Ju Haran.

457
00:24:09,887 --> 00:24:12,639
You don't believe me?
Let me show you the contract she signed!

458
00:24:13,348 --> 00:24:14,349
Where is it?

459
00:24:15,559 --> 00:24:16,727
I'll get it!

460
00:24:22,566 --> 00:24:24,359
[footsteps stomping]

461
00:24:24,943 --> 00:24:26,987
It's here!
This one!

462
00:24:27,529 --> 00:24:30,991
[whimpering]

463
00:24:31,950 --> 00:24:33,494
What are you doing?

464
00:24:36,622 --> 00:24:37,664
[Gitae] Boss.

465
00:24:37,748 --> 00:24:39,458
Hand it over!

466
00:24:39,541 --> 00:24:41,543
[Gitae] They think we're the ones
who stole the casket!

467
00:24:43,629 --> 00:24:45,047
I'd like to see it now.

468
00:24:51,095 --> 00:24:53,347
Come and get it, you motherfucker.

469
00:24:53,430 --> 00:24:56,850
Wow. You're fucking stubborn.

470
00:24:58,227 --> 00:24:59,520
Keep him alive, okay?

471
00:25:01,230 --> 00:25:02,856
Wait!
[gasps]

472
00:25:06,902 --> 00:25:09,905
[blows landing]
[All grunting]

473
00:25:18,455 --> 00:25:21,458
[blade slicing]
[Henchman screaming]

474
00:25:29,925 --> 00:25:30,926
[blow lands]

475
00:25:33,637 --> 00:25:35,264
[glass shatters]

476
00:25:46,024 --> 00:25:48,610
[both groaning]

477
00:25:54,908 --> 00:25:57,494
[gunshot]
[groaning]

478
00:25:57,578 --> 00:25:58,579
[labored breathing]

479
00:25:58,662 --> 00:25:59,955
[gasps]

480
00:26:00,038 --> 00:26:01,707
[all breathing heavily]

481
00:26:01,790 --> 00:26:03,083
You fucking asshole!

482
00:26:03,876 --> 00:26:06,003
[glass shattering]

483
00:26:06,086 --> 00:26:07,546
[groans]

484
00:26:09,256 --> 00:26:10,841
Oh, fuck.

485
00:26:10,924 --> 00:26:13,677
[both grunting]

486
00:26:14,178 --> 00:26:16,263
[banging and grunting]

487
00:26:20,809 --> 00:26:21,894
[glass shatters]

488
00:26:24,188 --> 00:26:25,939
[panicked breathing]

489
00:26:26,023 --> 00:26:28,734
[both grunting]

490
00:26:30,152 --> 00:26:32,321
[pained groaning]

491
00:26:32,404 --> 00:26:33,739
Wait, wait, wait!

492
00:26:34,489 --> 00:26:38,035
Okay, okay! You win, Park!
You win, Park! You win, Park, okay?

493
00:26:38,118 --> 00:26:40,162
Just a sec.
Let's not do this.
STYLE
::cue()

494
00:26:40,245 --> 00:26:41,997
We'll let you go if you just apologize.

495
00:26:42,080 --> 00:26:43,624
[Woojin] We can just bring
any old document and-

496
00:26:43,707 --> 00:26:46,877
[screaming]
Shit, okay, never mind! I'm sorry, okay?

497
00:26:46,960 --> 00:26:48,545
Let's just find the casket!

498
00:26:48,629 --> 00:26:50,923
Then the Chairman'll spare your life,
right? Okay?

499
00:26:51,465 --> 00:26:53,050
I can explain everything.

500
00:26:53,133 --> 00:26:54,426
[Woojin screaming]

501
00:26:54,968 --> 00:26:56,011
Boss!

502
00:26:56,094 --> 00:26:57,512
[Gitae] Have you lost your mind?

503
00:26:57,596 --> 00:26:59,348
[Woojin groans]

504
00:26:59,431 --> 00:27:01,767
Shit. Fuck!

505
00:27:03,435 --> 00:27:04,603
[groaning]

506
00:27:05,103 --> 00:27:08,065
[pained groans]

507
00:27:08,148 --> 00:27:10,192
You wanna save him,
you better take him to the hospital.

508
00:27:10,275 --> 00:27:13,028
-[Hocheol grunts]
-[gagging]

509
00:27:15,530 --> 00:27:16,823
Boss!

510
00:27:16,907 --> 00:27:18,325
Oh, man.

511
00:27:18,909 --> 00:27:20,827
[door creaking]

512
00:27:20,911 --> 00:27:22,829
[Jinman] What the-
is Park running away?

513
00:27:22,913 --> 00:27:25,290
Shit. Shit.

514
00:27:25,832 --> 00:27:27,125
This fucking...

515
00:27:27,209 --> 00:27:29,461
[grunting]

516
00:27:31,672 --> 00:27:34,675
[car engine turns over]

517
00:27:41,890 --> 00:27:43,225
Oh, sh-

518
00:27:51,858 --> 00:27:54,361
What the fuck is even going on?

519
00:27:54,444 --> 00:27:57,406
Hey, what happened here?
Heo Donggu, what just happened?

520
00:27:57,489 --> 00:27:58,657
[Gitae] Oh, fuck!

521
00:27:58,740 --> 00:28:01,118
What do you think happened?
Just take a look around!

522
00:28:01,201 --> 00:28:03,328
Ju Haran, I'm looking for her.
Have you seen her?

523
00:28:03,412 --> 00:28:06,164
Ju Haran? Well, I dunno.
Look at this place. I dunno.

524
00:28:06,248 --> 00:28:08,792
I saw her walk in here with my own eyes,
you asshole!

525
00:28:08,875 --> 00:28:10,752
[Donggu] What are you talking about?
Nobody came here!

526
00:28:10,836 --> 00:28:12,254
Can't you see this mess?

527
00:28:12,337 --> 00:28:14,423
You motherfucker! If you're lying to me,
I swear I'll fucking kill you.

528
00:28:14,506 --> 00:28:16,925
I'm not lying! Why would I?
I'm not lying to you! I swear!

529
00:28:17,009 --> 00:28:18,010
[Gitae] Detective Kim!

530
00:28:18,093 --> 00:28:19,386
Over here!

531
00:28:19,928 --> 00:28:21,179
Help me out!

532
00:28:21,263 --> 00:28:22,848
-[Gitae] Please, hurry!
-This fucking...

533
00:28:22,931 --> 00:28:25,017
[Gitae] Detective Kim!
Come on, hurry up!

534
00:28:25,100 --> 00:28:27,602
-Get over here! Come on, hurry!
-What happened to Chief Cheon?

535
00:28:27,686 --> 00:28:28,895
[Gitae] Come on, get over here!

536
00:28:28,979 --> 00:28:30,981
[both speaking at once]

537
00:28:31,064 --> 00:28:32,315
[Jinman] Here we go.

538
00:28:33,150 --> 00:28:35,068
Get him out of here.

539
00:28:35,152 --> 00:28:36,319
-Stay with us, Chief Cheon!
-Shit.

540
00:28:36,403 --> 00:28:39,448
If you die, we'll all end up dead!
Come on, we gotta move!

541
00:28:39,531 --> 00:28:41,408
[Cheon coughing]

542
00:28:43,035 --> 00:28:44,995
Come on!

543
00:28:45,871 --> 00:28:47,247
Shit.

544
00:28:47,330 --> 00:28:48,915
[cell phone buzzing]
Oh!

545
00:28:49,332 --> 00:28:50,375
Hello? Heeju?

546
00:28:50,917 --> 00:28:52,502
Tell me what the fuck
is goin' on in there!

547
00:28:52,586 --> 00:28:54,337
[Heeju] Woogy, you have to run.

548
00:28:54,421 --> 00:28:56,339
Detective Kim is heading your way.

549
00:28:57,049 --> 00:28:58,300
What are you gonna-
[phone beeps]

550
00:28:58,383 --> 00:28:59,384
Hello?

551
00:29:00,385 --> 00:29:01,386
Shit.

552
00:29:01,470 --> 00:29:04,181
[Gitae] Chief Cheon!
Please, please, don't die!

553
00:29:04,848 --> 00:29:06,892
-Please don't die!
-[grunts]

554
00:29:06,975 --> 00:29:08,685
[Gitae] We're in big trouble.

555
00:29:11,772 --> 00:29:13,106
[Donggu] No!

556
00:29:13,899 --> 00:29:15,025
They're all gone.

557
00:29:15,108 --> 00:29:16,943
[both breathing heavily]

558
00:29:19,029 --> 00:29:20,614
You can come out now.

559
00:29:22,407 --> 00:29:24,493
[footsteps on broken glass]

560
00:29:32,292 --> 00:29:33,293
[Donggu] Listen.

561
00:29:33,877 --> 00:29:35,045
Let's make a deal.

562
00:29:36,671 --> 00:29:38,924
Those men,
the ones that were here,

563
00:29:39,007 --> 00:29:40,383
I'm not like them at all.

564
00:29:41,218 --> 00:29:42,886
[Donggu] And I'm not that greedy, either.

565
00:29:43,804 --> 00:29:46,306
I'm not ambitious.

566
00:29:46,389 --> 00:29:48,767
All I'd like is to live a long life.

567
00:29:49,518 --> 00:29:53,563
And drugs, I'm out of that business.
I cut all connections ten years ago!

568
00:29:53,647 --> 00:29:55,023
I'm my own man now.

569
00:29:55,857 --> 00:29:57,109
The casket...

570
00:29:58,360 --> 00:30:01,321
Listen, shit, I really don't care
about it at all.

571
00:30:02,239 --> 00:30:04,533
Why else would I hide you in that cabinet?

572
00:30:04,616 --> 00:30:08,078
I hid you and I didn't tell those guys
that you're actually Kim Heeju,

573
00:30:08,161 --> 00:30:09,412
not Ju Haran.

574
00:30:11,915 --> 00:30:13,333
So what do you want from me?

575
00:30:15,836 --> 00:30:17,170
The transport fee.

576
00:30:18,380 --> 00:30:19,673
Ten gold bars.

577
00:30:20,340 --> 00:30:21,466
One billion won?

578
00:30:23,426 --> 00:30:25,095
We can negotiate, too.

579
00:30:25,178 --> 00:30:28,014
And also, uh,
after sales service?

580
00:30:28,098 --> 00:30:30,475
I'll take full responsibility
for everything right up till the end!

581
00:30:30,559 --> 00:30:31,560
I swear it!

582
00:30:33,311 --> 00:30:34,479
[Donggu] I mean it.

583
00:30:35,105 --> 00:30:36,648
[car alarm beeps]

584
00:30:36,731 --> 00:30:39,442
[Donggu inhales]
Look, that car over there.

585
00:30:39,943 --> 00:30:42,946
It's collateral I got yesterday.
You can take it. It's on me.

586
00:30:43,864 --> 00:30:45,365
I haven't even taken it to the garage yet.

587
00:30:45,448 --> 00:30:48,952
Feel free to drive it as much as you want,
and then get rid of it.

588
00:30:49,035 --> 00:30:51,830
[car engine revving]
STYLE
::cue()

589
00:31:02,757 --> 00:31:04,301
You can rest now.

590
00:31:07,512 --> 00:31:10,015
[♪ tense music]

591
00:31:10,098 --> 00:31:12,684
No need to make a big deal out of it.
Just have him cremated.

592
00:31:12,767 --> 00:31:13,768
Yes, sir.

593
00:31:14,311 --> 00:31:16,771
-Let Kim Jinman take care of the rest.
-Yes, sir.

594
00:31:17,189 --> 00:31:18,690
Have you found Park Hocheol yet?

595
00:31:19,649 --> 00:31:20,775
No.

596
00:31:20,859 --> 00:31:21,860
What?

597
00:31:23,278 --> 00:31:26,198
Get out there and find him immediately
before I rip each and every one of you

598
00:31:26,281 --> 00:31:27,616
-into fucking pieces!
-Right away.

599
00:31:36,416 --> 00:31:38,043
[Chairman Ahn] Are you doing okay, Ko?

600
00:31:38,710 --> 00:31:39,878
Yes, I'm okay, sir.

601
00:31:41,421 --> 00:31:43,673
[Chairman Ahn] Did you really not know
that Park had a lead?

602
00:31:44,591 --> 00:31:46,176
On the casket?

603
00:31:46,676 --> 00:31:50,430
[Jinman] Well, I hadn't really considered
that he would still be after it, sir.

604
00:31:50,513 --> 00:31:54,726
Honestly, uh,
I thought he'd gone back to Yes Money

605
00:31:54,809 --> 00:31:56,728
-and just given up on it.
-Whatever.

606
00:31:56,811 --> 00:31:59,272
Now bring me either Lee Dokyung
or Ju Haran.

607
00:31:59,356 --> 00:32:02,734
You're supposed to be the expert on this.
Just do your job.

608
00:32:02,817 --> 00:32:04,653
Then I'll get 'em to talk.

609
00:32:05,445 --> 00:32:07,072
Let's stick to what we're good at.

610
00:32:07,864 --> 00:32:08,865
Yes, sir.

611
00:32:09,449 --> 00:32:13,286
But if Park Hocheol finds that girl
or the casket before you do...

612
00:32:14,412 --> 00:32:16,748
...you can kiss one of your ears goodbye.

613
00:32:16,831 --> 00:32:17,999
[Jinman grunts]

614
00:32:24,798 --> 00:32:27,801
HAENGBOK PAWNSHOP

615
00:32:32,764 --> 00:32:35,767
[door rattling]

616
00:32:39,980 --> 00:32:42,983
[distant clocks quietly ticking]

617
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:53,576
[door creaks]

618
00:33:04,004 --> 00:33:06,172
[grunts]

619
00:33:06,256 --> 00:33:07,257
[clunks]

620
00:33:10,093 --> 00:33:12,220
[gold bars scraping]

621
00:33:18,893 --> 00:33:21,896
[♪ dramatic music]

622
00:33:33,033 --> 00:33:34,617
[exhales]

623
00:33:46,338 --> 00:33:47,756
[cell phone vibrating]

624
00:33:48,089 --> 00:33:51,217
INCOMING CALL
SUNOK

625
00:33:52,594 --> 00:33:53,970
[vibrating continues]

626
00:33:54,054 --> 00:33:55,096
[phone clicks]

627
00:33:56,348 --> 00:33:57,349
Hello?

628
00:33:58,558 --> 00:33:59,976
[Sunok] Can I see you for a bit?

629
00:34:03,188 --> 00:34:04,189
Now?

630
00:34:06,149 --> 00:34:07,359
Uh...

631
00:34:08,818 --> 00:34:09,903
Okay.

632
00:34:10,945 --> 00:34:11,946
Be right there.
STYLE
::cue()

633
00:34:14,491 --> 00:34:15,492
[phone beeps]

634
00:34:17,952 --> 00:34:19,996
Ah, dammit.

635
00:34:20,080 --> 00:34:23,083
[car engine revving]

636
00:34:38,515 --> 00:34:41,518
[inhales on cigarette]

637
00:34:46,272 --> 00:34:50,902
VEHICLE TRANSFER CERTIFICATE
JU HARAN

638
00:34:50,985 --> 00:34:52,112
Ju Haran.

639
00:34:52,195 --> 00:34:54,656
I've heard that name before.
Fuck.

640
00:34:56,533 --> 00:34:57,742
Dammit.

641
00:34:59,411 --> 00:35:00,620
[exhales]

642
00:35:02,997 --> 00:35:04,791
That's the bitch I killed.

643
00:35:08,044 --> 00:35:09,045
[exhales]

644
00:35:10,839 --> 00:35:12,173
[chuckles]

645
00:35:12,632 --> 00:35:19,639
YES MONEY

646
00:35:25,687 --> 00:35:27,063
[inhales]

647
00:35:36,156 --> 00:35:38,491
[knocking on door]
[Moonsu] Boss.

648
00:35:38,575 --> 00:35:40,118
-Boss.
-[Gitae] What?

649
00:35:40,201 --> 00:35:42,120
Did you see a ghost or something?

650
00:35:42,203 --> 00:35:44,330
[all gasping]

651
00:35:45,206 --> 00:35:46,332
[door closes]

652
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:48,084
Sir, what're...

653
00:35:50,503 --> 00:35:52,422
Nobody saw anything,
so keep your mouth shut.

654
00:35:53,673 --> 00:35:55,258
And no makin' any phone calls!

655
00:35:55,341 --> 00:35:56,801
-[Both] Yes, sir.
-[Gitae] Now get the fuck out.

656
00:35:56,885 --> 00:35:57,969
Shut the door.

657
00:35:58,970 --> 00:36:00,680
[Gitae exhales]
Why'd you come here?

658
00:36:01,973 --> 00:36:03,391
[door closes]

659
00:36:03,475 --> 00:36:04,684
You know you're being hunted.

660
00:36:04,768 --> 00:36:07,103
The Geumseong guys
are all over looking for you.

661
00:36:07,187 --> 00:36:08,855
[exhales]

662
00:36:08,938 --> 00:36:10,273
Where else should I go?

663
00:36:11,316 --> 00:36:12,609
This here is my turf.

664
00:36:13,485 --> 00:36:15,028
You know Chief Cheon died, right?

665
00:36:15,487 --> 00:36:16,571
He was cremated.

666
00:36:17,280 --> 00:36:19,115
-Yeah?
-Leave Jeongsan.

667
00:36:19,866 --> 00:36:21,826
Chairman Ahn will find out you were here.

668
00:36:21,910 --> 00:36:23,453
And then he'll murder us both.

669
00:36:24,204 --> 00:36:25,663
[exhales]

670
00:36:25,747 --> 00:36:26,998
Where's Ju Haran?

671
00:36:29,584 --> 00:36:30,585
I don't know.

672
00:36:32,337 --> 00:36:34,130
The Geumseong guys must be looking
for her.

673
00:36:35,507 --> 00:36:36,508
Gitae.

674
00:36:38,843 --> 00:36:40,637
Do you know who Ju Haran is?

675
00:36:42,055 --> 00:36:43,097
No, who?

676
00:36:43,598 --> 00:36:44,933
You know Gu Jaok, right?

677
00:36:45,767 --> 00:36:47,894
She's the largest backer in Gangwon.

678
00:36:49,187 --> 00:36:52,816
There's no one in Jeongsan who hasn't
set foot on land that old lady owns.

679
00:36:53,650 --> 00:36:55,735
Ju Haran is her granddaughter.

680
00:36:55,819 --> 00:36:56,820
What?

681
00:36:57,654 --> 00:36:58,822
Around a year ago...

682
00:36:59,781 --> 00:37:03,701
...Chairman Ahn wanted to buy the 2%
of Gu's stake in Gold Land.

683
00:37:05,537 --> 00:37:08,498
That would have made him Gold Land's
biggest shareholder.

684
00:37:08,998 --> 00:37:10,959
However, Ms. Gu knew what he was doing...

685
00:37:12,377 --> 00:37:14,420
...and she refused to hand over her stake.

686
00:37:15,171 --> 00:37:17,674
So I found her collateral,
and took it from her.

687
00:37:19,259 --> 00:37:20,260
Ju Haran.

688
00:37:21,094 --> 00:37:22,720
[Gitae] So what's going on?

689
00:37:23,221 --> 00:37:27,892
If Ju is her granddaughter,
she took the casket...

690
00:37:29,018 --> 00:37:31,187
...is Ms. Gu the one behind all this?

691
00:37:31,271 --> 00:37:33,231
No, that's not it.

692
00:37:35,483 --> 00:37:36,943
Ju Haran's already dead.
STYLE
::cue()

693
00:37:37,944 --> 00:37:39,112
I killed her.

694
00:37:40,113 --> 00:37:42,907
Mr. Jin took care of the body
and dumped it at the farm.

695
00:37:43,575 --> 00:37:46,578
Well then, who's the Ju Haran
with the casket now?

696
00:37:46,661 --> 00:37:48,288
She's a fake.

697
00:37:48,371 --> 00:37:50,123
[Hocheol] Someone's pretending
to be Ju Haran,

698
00:37:50,206 --> 00:37:51,875
and they've even been using her ID.

699
00:37:53,126 --> 00:37:54,586
But as you probably know...

700
00:37:55,879 --> 00:37:58,089
...we're supposed to keep hold
of every ID card.

701
00:37:58,965 --> 00:38:00,508
[inhales]

702
00:38:01,259 --> 00:38:04,012
That's right. ID card.

703
00:38:06,973 --> 00:38:07,974
[Gitae] Let's see.

704
00:38:08,057 --> 00:38:09,434
Fuck.

705
00:38:09,517 --> 00:38:10,852
Where is it?

706
00:38:20,236 --> 00:38:22,530
[breathing heavily]

707
00:38:23,072 --> 00:38:24,073
[Gitae] What's this?

708
00:38:27,201 --> 00:38:29,078
Her ID card is missing.

709
00:38:32,916 --> 00:38:35,001
[stammering]
I didn't do it!

710
00:38:35,877 --> 00:38:37,086
[Hocheol] Then who was it?

711
00:38:37,921 --> 00:38:39,130
Who has access to them?

712
00:38:42,884 --> 00:38:44,135
Someone with access.

713
00:38:44,218 --> 00:38:45,470
Who's here alone.

714
00:38:46,262 --> 00:38:47,263
Woogy.

715
00:38:48,097 --> 00:38:50,475
[Gitae] That fucking punk that handles
the office supplies and the cleaning,

716
00:38:50,558 --> 00:38:51,851
all that stuff.

717
00:38:51,935 --> 00:38:53,603
Where's that bastard now?

718
00:38:53,686 --> 00:38:55,688
He tried to leave the company recently.

719
00:38:56,564 --> 00:38:57,732
That piece of shit.

720
00:38:59,192 --> 00:39:00,234
Hey, Moonsu!

721
00:39:01,110 --> 00:39:03,029
-Yes, Boss?
-[Gitae] You work with Woogy, right?

722
00:39:03,279 --> 00:39:04,280
Yes.

723
00:39:04,364 --> 00:39:06,866
Go find him!
Find him and bring him here!

724
00:39:06,950 --> 00:39:08,326
But Woogy already quit.

725
00:39:08,826 --> 00:39:10,119
Yeah, no shit, you dumb ass!

726
00:39:10,203 --> 00:39:12,080
So fucking bring him to me right now!

727
00:39:12,413 --> 00:39:13,414
Yes, right away.

728
00:39:13,498 --> 00:39:15,083
[door creaks]

729
00:39:16,000 --> 00:39:18,378
[distant footsteps stomping away]

730
00:39:18,461 --> 00:39:21,172
So, what are you gonna do now, Boss?

731
00:39:21,255 --> 00:39:22,507
[Hocheol] What about you?

732
00:39:22,590 --> 00:39:24,008
What are you gonna do?

733
00:39:25,343 --> 00:39:27,178
I'm already tracking down
the fake Ju Haran

734
00:39:27,261 --> 00:39:28,596
and I'm close to finding her.

735
00:39:30,306 --> 00:39:33,351
You can go get that thief
who stole her ID card from us.

736
00:39:33,434 --> 00:39:35,353
After that, we find the casket.

737
00:39:35,812 --> 00:39:36,813
[Gitae] So then...

738
00:39:37,397 --> 00:39:41,234
Wait a sec. Find the casket.
I know that's what you want.

739
00:39:42,110 --> 00:39:44,404
But we'll need to double cross Geumseong
for it.

740
00:39:45,238 --> 00:39:46,990
Do you really think that's worth it?

741
00:39:49,242 --> 00:39:51,035
You don't even know what's inside of it,
do you?

742
00:39:51,119 --> 00:39:52,829
Obviously drugs!

743
00:39:52,912 --> 00:39:54,914
They're a pain in the ass to sell,
ya know?

744
00:39:55,415 --> 00:39:57,041
Gold bars.

745
00:39:58,626 --> 00:39:59,836
One ton.

746
00:40:01,421 --> 00:40:03,631
It's worth 150 billion won.

747
00:40:09,220 --> 00:40:11,597
Now do you get why I turned against Ahn?

748
00:40:13,224 --> 00:40:14,684
[exhales]

749
00:40:16,185 --> 00:40:17,186
But...

750
00:40:19,105 --> 00:40:22,608
...if it's that kind of money,
Chairman Ahn's not just gonna give up.

751
00:40:23,484 --> 00:40:26,904
If he loses that casket,
he'll end up in one of his own.

752
00:40:26,988 --> 00:40:28,948
[Hocheol] That's the investment money
from Cambodia

753
00:40:29,032 --> 00:40:30,825
for the joint Gold Resort development.

754
00:40:31,576 --> 00:40:35,163
If the deal falls through
and they don't get their principal back...

755
00:40:37,331 --> 00:40:38,958
...they're not just gonna
let him walk away.

756
00:40:40,710 --> 00:40:42,336
[Hocheol] Now, you need to decide.

757
00:40:45,506 --> 00:40:47,050
Whose side are you on?

758
00:40:50,136 --> 00:40:51,596
'Cause I'm all in.

759
00:40:52,346 --> 00:40:54,307
[inhales deeply]

760
00:40:54,390 --> 00:40:55,975
[exhales]

761
00:40:56,059 --> 00:40:58,394
[cigarette rubbing on ashtray]
STYLE
::cue()

762
00:41:20,291 --> 00:41:21,375
You're here.

763
00:41:21,459 --> 00:41:22,585
Yeah.

764
00:41:26,589 --> 00:41:28,216
That a side effect of the chemo?

765
00:41:29,592 --> 00:41:31,552
[Jinman] Well, at least
you're getting treatment.

766
00:41:31,636 --> 00:41:32,804
You'll be good soon.

767
00:41:35,640 --> 00:41:37,016
Tomorrow's my surgery.

768
00:41:37,975 --> 00:41:39,811
Really? That's good to hear.

769
00:41:40,728 --> 00:41:41,896
I hope it goes well.

770
00:41:43,231 --> 00:41:44,482
[Jinman] Better sooner than later.

771
00:41:48,277 --> 00:41:49,529
Will your niece be here?

772
00:41:49,612 --> 00:41:50,613
No.

773
00:41:54,450 --> 00:41:56,452
I called because I wanted
to see your face.

774
00:41:58,621 --> 00:42:00,706
Might be the last time I see you.

775
00:42:01,332 --> 00:42:04,001
What are you talking about?
Come on.

776
00:42:05,002 --> 00:42:06,003
Don't know.

777
00:42:07,630 --> 00:42:08,673
[grunts]

778
00:42:08,756 --> 00:42:10,216
I just have a feeling it might.

779
00:42:10,925 --> 00:42:12,385
[Jinman] You're talking nonsense now.

780
00:42:13,010 --> 00:42:14,095
Jeez.

781
00:42:14,178 --> 00:42:15,179
[clicks tongue]

782
00:42:16,556 --> 00:42:17,682
Could...

783
00:42:17,765 --> 00:42:19,016
[inhales]

784
00:42:19,100 --> 00:42:21,519
Could you give me a bath tonight?

785
00:42:22,311 --> 00:42:23,479
A bath?

786
00:42:24,355 --> 00:42:25,356
Mm-hmm.

787
00:42:27,275 --> 00:42:28,484
You remember...

788
00:42:30,695 --> 00:42:32,947
...when we were young
and I'd come home drunk...

789
00:42:33,573 --> 00:42:34,991
...you would help wash me up?

790
00:42:35,074 --> 00:42:36,117
[chuckles]

791
00:42:38,494 --> 00:42:39,871
I did?

792
00:42:40,830 --> 00:42:42,081
If I'm going to die...

793
00:42:44,458 --> 00:42:46,460
...I wanna die with some grace.

794
00:42:48,880 --> 00:42:51,883
[water running]

795
00:42:55,136 --> 00:42:56,220
[Sunok] Looking back...

796
00:42:57,972 --> 00:43:00,224
...that really was the spring time
of my life.

797
00:43:03,436 --> 00:43:04,687
Living in Namju.

798
00:43:07,690 --> 00:43:08,816
With you.

799
00:43:08,900 --> 00:43:11,027
The two of us in that little mining town.

800
00:43:12,778 --> 00:43:14,614
[water wringing from hair]

801
00:43:14,697 --> 00:43:15,698
Yeah.

802
00:43:17,033 --> 00:43:18,743
I barely remember those days.

803
00:43:23,873 --> 00:43:25,708
I resented you afterward.

804
00:43:26,918 --> 00:43:28,002
For quite a while.

805
00:43:31,797 --> 00:43:34,592
I always wished that you
hadn't disappeared so suddenly.

806
00:43:37,220 --> 00:43:38,554
Even if I stayed...

807
00:43:43,768 --> 00:43:45,228
[Jinman] Fucking hell.

808
00:43:45,311 --> 00:43:46,604
What kind of a man were you with?

809
00:43:46,687 --> 00:43:47,688
Fuck.

810
00:43:48,397 --> 00:43:49,649
[exhales]

811
00:43:49,732 --> 00:43:52,860
That's what happens when you're nothing
but bad luck.

812
00:43:53,569 --> 00:43:54,820
[clicks tongue]

813
00:43:54,904 --> 00:43:55,988
[Sunok] But back then...

814
00:43:56,906 --> 00:43:58,908
...it really was all I could do
to survive.

815
00:44:01,619 --> 00:44:03,704
The years I spent living with that man...

816
00:44:06,249 --> 00:44:07,708
...they were nothing but hell.

817
00:44:11,003 --> 00:44:13,589
It felt like it wouldn't end until one
of us died.

818
00:44:15,091 --> 00:44:16,133
[Sunok] But...

819
00:44:17,718 --> 00:44:19,428
...the thought of being
the first to die...

820
00:44:23,391 --> 00:44:24,684
...that seemed too unfair.

821
00:44:26,727 --> 00:44:27,853
[exhales]

822
00:44:27,937 --> 00:44:28,938
[Sunok] So then...

823
00:44:29,730 --> 00:44:30,898
...I killed him.

824
00:44:30,982 --> 00:44:32,149
[inhales]

825
00:44:33,985 --> 00:44:36,445
Han Cheoljung, that bastard.

826
00:44:38,906 --> 00:44:40,157
I killed him.

827
00:45:00,803 --> 00:45:02,013
[Jinman clears throat]
STYLE
::cue()

828
00:45:19,780 --> 00:45:21,198
[Jinman] I'll cut it now.

829
00:45:32,293 --> 00:45:34,670
[Jinman] You have a nice head shape.
Don't worry.

830
00:45:35,755 --> 00:45:38,966
There was that bald singer from the UK.
You used to like her, didn't you?

831
00:45:39,050 --> 00:45:41,677
You kind of look like her.
You look pretty.

832
00:45:41,761 --> 00:45:42,928
Not bad, right?

833
00:45:43,471 --> 00:45:44,722
[groans]

834
00:45:45,222 --> 00:45:46,307
[exhales]

835
00:45:55,524 --> 00:45:57,068
Heeju isn't my niece.

836
00:45:59,195 --> 00:46:00,654
She's my daughter.

837
00:46:00,738 --> 00:46:01,739
What?

838
00:46:06,702 --> 00:46:08,162
And you're her father.

839
00:46:10,122 --> 00:46:11,374
[Sunok] After you left...

840
00:46:12,249 --> 00:46:14,377
...I found out that I was pregnant.

841
00:46:16,837 --> 00:46:19,090
The house where we lived together
in Namju...

842
00:46:20,591 --> 00:46:22,009
...that's where Heeju was born.

843
00:46:23,260 --> 00:46:25,388
[chuckles]

844
00:46:26,222 --> 00:46:28,015
You're kidding, right?

845
00:46:28,641 --> 00:46:29,642
It's a joke.

846
00:46:31,268 --> 00:46:32,520
[Jinman] That doesn't make any sense.

847
00:46:33,354 --> 00:46:35,773
I was going to keep it
a secret until I died.

848
00:46:36,941 --> 00:46:39,151
I didn't think I'd see you again.

849
00:46:39,985 --> 00:46:41,070
Okay, then.

850
00:46:41,153 --> 00:46:42,446
Why say all of this now?

851
00:46:44,073 --> 00:46:45,074
Jinman.

852
00:46:46,617 --> 00:46:48,619
[grunting]

853
00:46:51,163 --> 00:46:52,164
Heeju...

854
00:46:53,290 --> 00:46:56,127
I think she's unhappy nowadays.

855
00:46:57,711 --> 00:46:59,255
She's in trouble.

856
00:47:00,798 --> 00:47:02,258
And it's all because of me, I know.

857
00:47:03,634 --> 00:47:06,303
I just can't be buried with all
of that guilt.

858
00:47:07,054 --> 00:47:09,223
[Sunok] Not when it was me
who made her that way.

859
00:47:10,266 --> 00:47:12,476
I've always told her she
was a luckless brat...

860
00:47:13,602 --> 00:47:15,438
...born from a luckless bitch.

861
00:47:17,731 --> 00:47:18,732
So could you...

862
00:47:19,775 --> 00:47:21,402
...could you please take care of her?

863
00:47:23,404 --> 00:47:25,614
[Sunok] Don't let her ruin
her life any further.

864
00:47:25,948 --> 00:47:28,534
Keep her out of prison
and safe from bad men.

865
00:47:28,617 --> 00:47:29,910
[sniffles]

866
00:47:29,994 --> 00:47:31,495
You're a police officer.

867
00:47:32,079 --> 00:47:33,122
And her dad.

868
00:47:33,706 --> 00:47:36,792
-So you need to protect your daughter now.
-[Jinman] Enough.

869
00:47:38,377 --> 00:47:39,545
[exhales]
Hey.

870
00:47:40,963 --> 00:47:43,549
Listen, I just have to ask,
how am I supposed to believe you?

871
00:47:44,008 --> 00:47:45,009
Huh?

872
00:47:45,801 --> 00:47:49,054
You were a working girl.
A lady of the night.

873
00:47:49,138 --> 00:47:50,389
[Sunok] What?

874
00:47:50,473 --> 00:47:51,724
[scoffs]

875
00:47:51,807 --> 00:47:53,392
You mean when I was a hostess?

876
00:47:54,101 --> 00:47:55,102
[Jinman] Yeah.

877
00:47:55,394 --> 00:47:56,395
I mean...

878
00:47:57,146 --> 00:47:59,565
...seriously, how the fuck would
I know whose daughter she is?

879
00:48:00,149 --> 00:48:01,150
I wouldn't.

880
00:48:01,233 --> 00:48:02,318
I do, though.

881
00:48:03,986 --> 00:48:05,613
You were the only one I was with then.

882
00:48:10,826 --> 00:48:13,537
[inhales]
Shit, this is really fucked.

883
00:48:17,791 --> 00:48:19,376
[Jinman groans]

884
00:48:20,920 --> 00:48:22,338
[smacks lips]

885
00:48:22,421 --> 00:48:24,089
[Jinman] Shit.

886
00:48:27,676 --> 00:48:28,677
[clicks tongue]

887
00:48:30,012 --> 00:48:34,141
Hey. Have you told her, you know, that-

888
00:48:34,225 --> 00:48:35,809
that I'm, uh-I'm her dad?

889
00:48:35,893 --> 00:48:37,686
Or, does she know?

890
00:48:38,646 --> 00:48:39,688
I haven't.

891
00:48:41,273 --> 00:48:43,108
Heeju believes her father's dead.

892
00:48:45,903 --> 00:48:49,949
Would you tell your daughter
that her father was a gambling addict...

893
00:48:50,908 --> 00:48:52,868
...who ran off and abandoned her?

894
00:48:53,536 --> 00:48:55,079
That's good, then, yeah?

895
00:48:55,663 --> 00:48:57,414
Just keep it that way, okay?

896
00:48:58,207 --> 00:49:00,292
'Cause I-
I'm not her father.

897
00:49:00,376 --> 00:49:02,461
[Jinman] Got it?
Don't tell her.

898
00:49:03,170 --> 00:49:06,048
If you tell her I'm her father,
or anything like that,

899
00:49:06,131 --> 00:49:09,593
you, me, and her,
we're all gonna be fucked.

900
00:49:11,595 --> 00:49:13,347
The three of us will die.

901
00:49:13,430 --> 00:49:14,431
[Jinman] Understand?

902
00:49:15,599 --> 00:49:17,601
So stop saying nonsense.

903
00:49:18,519 --> 00:49:19,687
Seriously.

904
00:49:19,770 --> 00:49:20,771
[clicks tongue]

905
00:49:31,532 --> 00:49:34,326
[door opens and closes]

906
00:49:34,410 --> 00:49:35,911
[exhales]
STYLE
::cue()

907
00:49:49,049 --> 00:49:50,342
[brakes squeak]

908
00:49:52,052 --> 00:49:55,055
[chains rattling]

909
00:50:02,104 --> 00:50:05,107
[door scraping]

910
00:50:21,415 --> 00:50:22,708
[brakes squeak]

911
00:50:32,468 --> 00:50:34,094
[beeping]

912
00:50:37,306 --> 00:50:38,766
[creaking]

913
00:50:47,691 --> 00:50:49,401
[exhales]

914
00:50:50,361 --> 00:50:53,030
[Heeju] Mokcheon Port, 9:00 p.m. tomorrow.

915
00:50:55,491 --> 00:50:56,533
See you there.

916
00:51:05,250 --> 00:51:08,253
[inhales and exhales sharply]

917
00:51:11,006 --> 00:51:14,009
[cell phone vibrating]

918
00:51:16,220 --> 00:51:18,555
INCOMING CALL
AUNTIE MIJA

919
00:51:20,516 --> 00:51:21,975
Hey, Auntie.

920
00:51:22,476 --> 00:51:23,769
Hey.

921
00:51:23,852 --> 00:51:25,229
Are you coming today?

922
00:51:27,147 --> 00:51:28,691
[Mija] Why aren't you saying anything?

923
00:51:28,774 --> 00:51:29,858
[exhales]

924
00:51:29,942 --> 00:51:32,986
You should be here.
Your mom might be dying.

925
00:51:33,570 --> 00:51:35,739
Ah, I just have a bad feeling.

926
00:51:35,823 --> 00:51:37,491
I really think you should come.

927
00:51:39,576 --> 00:51:40,661
Okay.

928
00:51:45,541 --> 00:51:46,750
[exhales]

929
00:51:51,755 --> 00:51:52,881
[Mija] Sunok.

930
00:51:53,382 --> 00:51:55,050
Everything will be all right.

931
00:51:55,759 --> 00:51:58,095
Just stay calm. Okay?

932
00:51:58,887 --> 00:51:59,888
RESTRICTED AREA
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

933
00:51:59,972 --> 00:52:02,266
Oh, and Heeju will be here soon.

934
00:52:02,933 --> 00:52:03,976
See you later!

935
00:52:04,810 --> 00:52:07,813
[♪ dramatic music]

936
00:52:13,694 --> 00:52:19,366
GANGWON SAEBAEK HOSPITAL

937
00:52:20,409 --> 00:52:21,869
[Heeju] Is it over already?

938
00:52:21,952 --> 00:52:22,953
Yeah.

939
00:52:23,036 --> 00:52:24,163
[sniffs]

940
00:52:24,913 --> 00:52:26,707
They closed her up right away.

941
00:52:28,959 --> 00:52:31,378
I spoke with the doctor
before I called you.

942
00:52:32,171 --> 00:52:34,798
They said from here on out,
chemo won't help her.

943
00:52:36,800 --> 00:52:38,427
So she should go home.

944
00:52:38,886 --> 00:52:41,096
And spend the rest
of her time with family.

945
00:52:41,180 --> 00:52:43,265
[breathing shakily]

946
00:52:43,348 --> 00:52:44,641
Where are you right now?

947
00:52:45,726 --> 00:52:47,311
Why aren't you over here?

948
00:52:50,773 --> 00:52:51,857
[phone beeps]

949
00:52:56,069 --> 00:52:57,529
[shudders]

950
00:53:01,742 --> 00:53:04,745
[machines beeping]

951
00:53:07,164 --> 00:53:10,167
[♪ dramatic music]

952
00:53:18,425 --> 00:53:19,885
Hi, Mom.

953
00:53:30,562 --> 00:53:33,690
GANGWON SAEBAEK HOSPITAL
EMERGENCY CENTER

954
00:53:36,151 --> 00:53:39,154
[breathing heavily]

955
00:54:09,601 --> 00:54:12,604
[♪ dramatic music continues]

956
00:54:40,632 --> 00:54:43,635
[♪ music continues]

